00:17:55.380 --> 00:18:00.190
those are the people that I work with mostly
in this kind of work. So I feel, I feel kind

00:18:00.190 --> 00:18:04.620
of like I have an advantage. I feel lucky
that any time I get to be the UN or really

00:18:04.620 --> 00:18:07.881
at the table with so many of the people that
are really leaders in the maternal and newborn

00:18:07.881 --> 00:18:14.150
child health sector, I feel like my classmates
would be so jealous. [laughs] And I've actually

00:18:14.150 --> 00:18:17.670
been able to employ a few of 'em. They been
helping us with some of the education modules

00:18:17.670 --> 00:18:22.710
and I really I love the experience. I'm taking
the slow track at the moment so I'll be there

00:18:22.710 --> 00:18:25.180
another year or so but I'm enjoying it immensely.

00:18:25.180 --> 00:18:28.500
&gt;&gt;Marisa: Very cool. So after this next question,
we'll go ahead and open it up to the audience.

00:18:28.500 --> 00:18:32.350
So if you have a question for Christy you
can go here to the mic so people can hear.

00:18:32.350 --> 00:18:36.960
But the last question is changing gears to
Google. Do you have a favorite Google product

00:18:36.960 --> 00:18:38.850
and how do you use it?

00:18:38.850 --> 00:18:39.850
[laughter]

00:18:39.850 --> 00:18:45.500
&gt;&gt;Christy Turlington: Well the ones that I
use like daily are -- I mean I constantly

