00:23:44.040 --> 00:23:49.910
guess it has certainly helped in a sense because
I sometimes have an opportunity to get some

00:23:49.910 --> 00:23:56.760
media attention. But I don't think like the
job itself had any real effect on it. It's

00:23:56.760 --> 00:24:00.660
just that it allowed me to really travel and
see the world a lot and I think feel a little

00:24:00.660 --> 00:24:06.630
bit more connected to a lot of women outside
of the community where I was raised and where

00:24:06.630 --> 00:24:13.390
I was brought up. So I guess the experience
of being able to travel definitely had something

00:24:13.390 --> 00:24:18.440
to do with it. And then the fact that I do
have some ability to be able to get some media

00:24:18.440 --> 00:24:24.440
attention. I think if I didn't have a deeper
knowledge, I don't know that it would be that

00:24:24.440 --> 00:24:25.440
effective.

00:24:25.440 --> 00:24:30.330
But the fact that I have made the commitment
to go deeper and to go back to school, I think

00:24:30.330 --> 00:24:34.310
will make me a more effective communicator
because it's one thing to communicate what

00:24:34.310 --> 00:24:39.400
you see and to tell stories and to go on trips
and to have your picture taken someplace.

00:24:39.400 --> 00:24:45.140
But it's another thing to take it to the next
level and to continue to go deeper and to,

00:24:45.140 --> 00:24:48.780
for me I really wanna be a part of the solutions
of this problem. I didn't wanna just come

00:24:48.780 --> 00:24:55.530
and observe and walk away. I'm deeply committed
to this and I don't know if being a fashion

00:24:55.530 --> 00:24:57.970
model has anything to do with that. [chuckles]

00:24:57.970 --> 00:25:01.910
&gt;&gt;female #2: Hi I'm Jacqueline. Thanks a lot
for taking on this issue because it's been

00:25:01.910 --> 00:25:06.240
a really neglected issue and we really need
people like you to champion it. So thank you.

00:25:06.240 --> 00:25:12.220
So a few of us also went with CARE on a maternal
mortality learning trip last year and we went

00:25:12.220 --> 00:25:15.930
to Sierra Leone and one of the things that
we learned when we were there is that there

00:25:15.930 --> 00:25:21.180
was one pediatrician for all of Sierra Leone.
I mean the country is just so decimated in

00:25:21.180 --> 00:25:25.900
terms of health resources. So obviously the
answer to improving maternal mortality has

00:25:25.900 --> 00:25:30.560
a lot to do with increasing foreign assistance
and development assistance and I was just

00:25:30.560 --> 00:25:35.870
wondering especially now given the cut backs
and given the sort of climate of fear and

00:25:35.870 --> 00:25:42.430
holding on to our resources to tightly, how
that's going. How you and Erin are taking

00:25:42.430 --> 00:25:45.000
on this issue and are you optimistic at all
and where do you think that's headed?

00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:50.280
&gt;&gt;Christy Turlington: That's a good point.
I mean right now is an incredibly tough time

00:25:50.280 --> 00:25:57.380
and the budgets are getting slashed on a daily
basis here and for international aid. I think

00:25:57.380 --> 00:26:00.930
because we know the next couple years are
gonna be rough, what we're hoping is some

00:26:00.930 --> 00:26:04.860
of the momentum that was built around maternal
mortality and maternal health in the last

00:26:04.860 --> 00:26:10.250
year, -- it was on the agenda for the first
time at the G8 last summer -- that all of

00:26:10.250 --> 00:26:15.560
that and some of the attention that Bill and
Linda Gates have brought to it and Sarah Brown,

00:26:15.560 --> 00:26:19.410
Gordon Brown's wife. I mean some of those
things have escalated the issue to now be

00:26:19.410 --> 00:26:21.470
-- it's on the agenda.

00:26:21.470 --> 00:26:28.210
So our priority is keeping it a focus so that
we don't fell back. The idea is like, "Okay

00:26:28.210 --> 00:26:32.700
we can't do a whole lot with aid right now
but we can sort of keep pushing along." And

00:26:32.700 --> 00:26:37.320
we believe that civil society hasn't really
been a part of this dialog yet. And we hope

00:26:37.320 --> 00:26:42.250
that the film and the exposure on something
like the Oprah Winfrey Network and our partnership

00:26:42.250 --> 00:26:47.140
with Starbucks and the CD we've created -- that
those are ways to really bring in everyday

00:26:47.140 --> 00:26:53.470
citizens, moms, family members to get to be
a part of this, to participate. And I mean

00:26:53.470 --> 00:26:58.520
we really envision us playing a big role -- like
that we actually can be a part of helping

00:26:58.520 --> 00:26:59.670
to bridge some of that funding gap that exists
now.

00:26:59.670 --> 00:27:06.690
&gt;&gt;Marisa: And we have a question about volunteering
and being able to help. Are there things that

00:27:06.690 --> 00:27:07.890
people can do from here?

00:27:07.890 --> 00:27:12.370
&gt;&gt;Christy Turlington: Yeah -- we often get
that question and we're trying to really identify

00:27:12.370 --> 00:27:19.670
a few ways that people can have meaningful
results. And some of those are volunteering.

00:27:19.670 --> 00:27:25.170
They might not mean you have to leave this
country. There are ways to be able to create

00:27:25.170 --> 00:27:30.770
watch parties and host parties and to learn
more so that you can then have a voice within

00:27:30.770 --> 00:27:35.710
your community and create your own constituency
around this issue and have your voice heard.

00:27:35.710 --> 00:27:40.360
Because there are so many women and girls
who do not have a voice and so my, the main

00:27:40.360 --> 00:27:44.050
thing that you can do that anyone could do
is to use your voice 'cause you have one.

00:27:44.050 --> 00:27:48.870
But the second thing is I mean we have, we're
trying to identify a few very easy ways, tangible

00:27:48.870 --> 00:27:53.240
ways and we have identified a few organizations
there you can donate phones, phones that you

00:27:53.240 --> 00:27:57.680
don't use anymore, that you've discarded.
We have ways that you can help support midwives

00:27:57.680 --> 00:28:03.240
and the education of midwives to get supplies
into their hands that they are better able

00:28:03.240 --> 00:28:05.240
to do a job.

00:28:05.240 --> 00:28:10.300
We're gonna have some of those ready for our
launch on May 7th and we do invite you to

00:28:10.300 --> 00:28:14.590
come back to the site and to look at it 'cause
we'll give you some very specific ideas and

00:28:14.590 --> 00:28:16.450
ways you can do things.

00:28:16.450 --> 00:28:21.100
&gt;&gt;Marisa: In addition to being on the Oprah
Winfrey Network, is it also going to be released

00:28:21.100 --> 00:28:24.951
more widely? How will people be able to see
it? They'll be able to see it on May 7th and

00:28:24.951 --> 00:28:25.951
--

00:28:25.951 --> 00:28:29.490
&gt;&gt;Christy Turlington: Yes, well OWN will be
our broadcast partner here and then they have

00:28:29.490 --> 00:28:32.590
the digital and video rights. So it will be
part of -- she's gonna have a documentary

00:28:32.590 --> 00:28:37.810
club kind of like her book club and we'll
be a part of that. And then OWN will also

00:28:37.810 --> 00:28:43.100
broadcast it in Canada under another network
called CORUS who's gonna be distributing OWN.

00:28:43.100 --> 00:28:47.630
And then we'll be doing also broadcasts in
France around their Mother's Day which is

