00:28:56.840 --> 00:29:00.980
Day is not an international, an internationally
celebrated event, but those are kind of key

00:29:00.980 --> 00:29:02.820
moments where it could be launched.

00:29:02.820 --> 00:29:05.890
And then we're continuing to travel with it
at global health conferences. I've been showing

00:29:05.890 --> 00:29:10.120
it for the last year since we launched at
Tribeca to really get it out there amongst

00:29:10.120 --> 00:29:11.120
the community.

00:29:11.120 --> 00:29:14.700
&gt;&gt;Marisa: How has making this film changed
your view on motherhood?

00:29:14.700 --> 00:29:18.870
&gt;&gt;Christy Turlington: Hmm. Well I think I
there's not a whole lot that I can complain

00:29:18.870 --> 00:29:23.830
about as a mom [laughs] or as a working person.
My mother will tell me all the time, "Oh you're

00:29:23.830 --> 00:29:26.870
working so hard. You really have to slow down."
And I said, "You have no idea what hard work

00:29:26.870 --> 00:29:31.850
is until you go out in the world." So the
stuff that I do, it's like the very least

00:29:31.850 --> 00:29:37.250
I can do because I can do it and I can choose
to do the things that I do and I can choose

00:29:37.250 --> 00:29:42.060
to donate my time and my energy to an issue
like this.

00:29:42.060 --> 00:29:48.480
I think the appreciation of having had the
health care workers that I had that helped

00:29:48.480 --> 00:29:53.090
me in my own situation while delivering, I
mean I have tremendous respect and did from

00:29:53.090 --> 00:29:59.950
day one for midwives and for doctors and for
nurses because they really are the unsung

00:29:59.950 --> 00:30:03.300
heroes around the world and I truly believe
that.

00:30:03.300 --> 00:30:09.370
And I think for my children, I'm the best
example I can be as a human being for them.

00:30:09.370 --> 00:30:14.110
Like that's my first priority and I think
by the stuff that I'm interested in, the things

00:30:14.110 --> 00:30:18.841
that I'm sort of pursuing, they're seeing
that and they're getting exposed to the world

00:30:18.841 --> 00:30:23.810
and the issues, the real issues that I think
really matter at a really young age. I think

00:30:23.810 --> 00:30:27.520
that's like an invaluable thing that I can
give them and I can't wait to be able to share

00:30:27.520 --> 00:30:31.770
more of the world with them and have them
help me. I can't wait to be side by side with

00:30:31.770 --> 00:30:36.170
my daughter working on these issues. So she's
seven and a half now I figure I give her another

00:30:36.170 --> 00:30:39.360
couple years and then [laughs] drag her on
the road with me. [laughs]

